    {# ===== FAQ ===== #}
    <section class="cs-ct-section">
      <h2 class="cs-ct-stitle">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--cs-gold)" stroke-width="2" width="26" height="26"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/><path d="M9.09 9a3 3 0 015.83 1c0 2-3 3-3 3"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12.01" y2="17"/></svg>
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <div class="cs-ct-faq">
        <details class="cs-ct-faq__item">
          <summary class="cs-ct-faq__q">How do I apply to an undergraduate CS programme?</summary>
          <div class="cs-ct-faq__a">
            <p>Applications to Stellenbosch University are made through the main <a href="https://www.sun.ac.za/english/Pages/Apply-Online.aspx" target="_blank">university application portal</a>. For CS-specific admission queries, contact <a href="mailto:undergrad@cs.sun.ac.za">undergrad@cs.sun.ac.za</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="cs-ct-faq__item">
          <summary class="cs-ct-faq__q">Can I visit the department in person?</summary>
          <div class="cs-ct-faq__a">
            <p>Yes! You&rsquo;re welcome to visit during office hours (Mon&ndash;Fri, 08:00&ndash;16:00). For a guided tour, email <a href="mailto:secretary@cs.sun.ac.za">secretary@cs.sun.ac.za</a> to arrange ahead of time.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="cs-ct-faq__item">
          <summary class="cs-ct-faq__q">How do I find a postgraduate research supervisor?</summary>
          <div class="cs-ct-faq__a">
            <p>Browse our <a href="/research">research groups page</a> to find areas that interest you, then contact <a href="mailto:postgrad@cs.sun.ac.za">postgrad@cs.sun.ac.za</a> to discuss potential supervisors. You can also reach out to specific staff members directly via the <a href="https://cs.sun.ac.za" target="_blank">department website</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="cs-ct-faq__item">
          <summary class="cs-ct-faq__q">Are there bursaries available for CS students?</summary>
          <div class="cs-ct-faq__a">
            <p>Yes. The department offers teaching assistant (TA) bursaries, and there are also university-wide bursaries, NSFAS funding, and industry-sponsored scholarships. See our <a href="/postgraduate/prospective">prospective students page</a> or contact the postgraduate office.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="cs-ct-faq__item">
          <summary class="cs-ct-faq__q">What are the admission requirements for Honours / Masters / PhD?</summary>
          <div class="cs-ct-faq__a">
            <p>Requirements vary by programme. See the <a href="/postgraduate/honours">Honours</a>, <a href="/postgraduate/masters">Master&rsquo;s</a>, or <a href="/postgraduate/phd">PhD</a> pages for detailed admission criteria, or email <a href="mailto:postgrad@cs.sun.ac.za">postgrad@cs.sun.ac.za</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

